From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 11:34:50 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon: unconditionally trace damon_region_aggregated

It is aimed to replace damon_aggregated tracepoint.  Trace it always.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 include/trace/events/damon.h | 4 +---
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/include/trace/events/damon.h b/include/trace/events/damon.h
index 8851727ae1627..4dfc9467ea4b5 100644
--- a/include/trace/events/damon.h
+++ b/include/trace/events/damon.h
@@ -132,15 +132,13 @@ TRACE_EVENT(damon_monitor_intervals_tune,
 	TP_printk("sample_us=%lu", __entry->sample_us)
 );
 
-TRACE_EVENT_CONDITION(damon_region_aggregated,
+TRACE_EVENT(damon_region_aggregated,
 
 	TP_PROTO(unsigned int target_id, struct damon_region *r,
 		unsigned int nr_regions, unsigned int nr_probes),
 
 	TP_ARGS(target_id, r, nr_regions, nr_probes),
 
-	TP_CONDITION(nr_probes > 0),
-
 	TP_STRUCT__entry(
 		__field(unsigned long, target_id)
 		__field(unsigned long, start)
-- 
2.47.3

